## AI Setup Tab (`apiKeysSection`)

**Required flow:** select provider (`preferredProviderSelect`) ‚Üí PATCH `preferred_provider` ‚Üí add BYOK for Gemini/OpenAI/Anthropic (Ollama needs no key) ‚Üí optional model for the active provider.

| Card / control ID | Shown when |
|-------------------|-----------|
| `providerSelectorCard` | Always (required pick) |
| `serverKeyNotice` | `use_vertex_ai` ‚Äî Vertex admin mode; no personal key |
| `ollamaNotice` | `preferred_provider === 'ollama'` |
| `byokNotice` | Cloud provider selected **and** no stored key for that provider ‚Äî **hidden when no provider is selected** |
| `userKeyNotice` | Active cloud provider has a stored key |
| `modelSelectorCard` | Credentials ready (key saved / Ollama) and not Vertex |

**Layout:** provider / BYOK / model cards use `.account-card.ai-setup-card` ‚Äî compact header + `.ai-setup-card-controls` (border-top, ends right after the dropdown or key row). Icons use `.account-icon--amber` for provider / BYOK / model.

**Saved indicator:** `#providerSavedIndicator` / `#modelSavedIndicator` sit **inline next to the card title** (not under or inside the dropdown). Fade via `.save-indicator` opacity like Preferences.

**API status** (`GET /api/v1/profile/api-key/status`): `preferred_provider`, `has_credentials`, `providers.{gemini|openai|anthropic|ollama}`, `models` per provider (from `utils/llm/models.py`), `use_vertex_ai` / `server_has_key` (Vertex-only for user gates).

**Key CRUD:** `POST /api-key` `{ provider, api_key }` (also activates that provider); `DELETE /api-key?provider=`; `POST /api-key/validate`. Ollama rejects key ops.

**BYOK form** (`byokNotice`): provider-specific subtitle + Get API Key link (`PROVIDER_KEY_LINKS` in `ui/src/dashboard-settings/api-keys.ts`). Input id remains `geminiApiKey` for DOM stability.

**Model selector:** options from status `models[preferred_provider]` via `populateModelSelect()` with friendly labels (`MODEL_LABELS` in preferences.ts / `utils/llm/models.py`). Switching `preferred_provider` clears `preferred_model`.

### Model allowlists (`utils/llm/models.py`)

| Provider | Default | Allowed ids |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| Gemini | `gemini-3.5-flash` | `gemini-3.5-flash`, `gemini-3.1-flash-lite`, `gemini-3.1-pro-preview`, `gemini-2.5-flash`, `gemini-2.5-pro` |
| OpenAI | `gpt-5.6-luna` | `gpt-5.6-luna`, `gpt-5.6-terra`, `gpt-5.6-sol`, `gpt-5.5`, `gpt-5.4-mini` |
| Anthropic | `claude-sonnet-5` | `claude-sonnet-5`, `claude-opus-4-8`, `claude-haiku-4-5`, `claude-fable-5`, `claude-sonnet-4-6` |
| Ollama | `qwen3.6` | `qwen3.6`, `gemma4`, `glm-4.7-flash`, `granite4.1`, `nemotron3`, `phi4` |

Do not re-add dead Gemini ids (`gemini-3-flash-preview`, `gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview`, `gemini-3-pro-preview`, `gemini-2.0-*`, `gemini-1.5-*`) or retired OpenAI/Anthropic names (`gpt-4o*`, `claude-sonnet-4-5` as primary, etc.).

**API key links:** Gemini ‚Üí `https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey`; OpenAI ‚Üí `https://platform.openai.com/api-keys`; Anthropic ‚Üí `https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys`.

